cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning 3D shapes from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper uses a generative model, specifically a convolutional neural network, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves differential rendering, which is a technique used in computer graphics (cs.GR). The method is unsupervised, meaning it does not require any manual annotation, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses adversarial training, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
